WEBVTT

00:41.332 --> 00:42.542
I mean…

00:46.629 --> 00:48.548
Let's not say anything for now.

00:50.675 --> 00:54.345
I can't say that it was a mistake,
that we should pretend…

00:57.849 --> 00:59.434
it never happened.

01:08.485 --> 01:10.487
Because it wasn't a mistake.

01:20.497 --> 01:21.498
We're here.

01:28.421 --> 01:29.464
Wait.

01:33.635 --> 01:36.971
Here. It's the last day
of the exhibition tomorrow.

01:46.106 --> 01:47.190
I'll be waiting.

01:53.947 --> 01:54.906
Goodbye, then.

01:57.826 --> 01:58.660
Right.

03:31.544 --> 03:34.172
LEE KYU-TAE SOLO EXHIBITION

05:15.481 --> 05:17.483
Stay there. I'll come to you.

05:37.795 --> 05:38.796
Sorry I'm late.

05:38.880 --> 05:40.340
No, it's okay.

05:43.551 --> 05:44.469
That's…

05:46.471 --> 05:48.222
Let's hurry. We're gonna be late.

05:49.515 --> 05:50.350
Right.

06:02.278 --> 06:03.613
Why were you late?

06:04.989 --> 06:06.324
What matters is I'm here.

06:07.617 --> 06:08.785
Why are you here?

06:10.203 --> 06:11.788
EPISODE 9
LIKE OR LOVE

06:11.871 --> 06:13.206
To see you.

06:24.801 --> 06:25.718
Are you okay?

06:27.428 --> 06:29.514
Of course. I'm totally fine.

06:43.444 --> 06:44.529
Drink this.

06:50.910 --> 06:51.911
I'll protect you.

07:13.015 --> 07:14.267
Yellow? Really?

07:15.017 --> 07:15.852
It's pretty!

07:18.980 --> 07:20.106
The V sign?

07:20.189 --> 07:21.107
Come here.

07:33.828 --> 07:35.621
Ta-da. I'm good, aren't I?

07:44.005 --> 07:45.089
Are you okay?

07:45.173 --> 07:46.674
-I've got this.
-You've got this?

07:51.220 --> 07:53.389
There are five of us,
so we need three toppings.

07:53.473 --> 07:54.891
-Lovely.
-Two kinds of noodles.

07:54.974 --> 07:57.393
-And cheese. Make that two.
-Glass noodles.

07:57.477 --> 08:00.563
Order jjolmyeon noodles, too,
with a side of dumplings.

08:00.646 --> 08:01.981
-Awesome.
-Love it!

08:02.940 --> 08:03.941
Let's eat by ourselves.

08:05.568 --> 08:06.569
Sounds good.

08:09.363 --> 08:10.698
Ta-da.

08:11.491 --> 08:13.451
Okay. Ta-da!

08:14.368 --> 08:15.786
That's so cute.

08:20.500 --> 08:22.376
How is it? Isn't it good?

08:25.213 --> 08:26.672
It's delicious.

08:27.757 --> 08:29.342
Let me try one.

08:29.425 --> 08:33.095
Why don't you try the pork cutlet first?
You shouldn't…

08:42.480 --> 08:44.232
It's way too salty. Are you okay?

08:44.315 --> 08:46.317
-I love it. Really.
-No. Don't eat it.

08:53.199 --> 08:54.200
Sounds delicious.

09:08.631 --> 09:09.507
Thank you.

09:10.007 --> 09:11.551
Here, let me pour you a drink.

09:20.309 --> 09:21.978
Two lids for two bottles!

09:23.104 --> 09:25.106
-I can handle just one glass.
-Whoa, no.

10:12.111 --> 10:16.490
Yes. For lunch,
I had tuna gimbap and jjolmyeon.

10:16.574 --> 10:17.408
My wrist?

10:17.992 --> 10:21.746
It's better than yesterday,
but I'm still struggling. Yeah.

10:22.371 --> 10:25.249
Okay. I'll call you back later.

10:27.710 --> 10:31.714
He calls me ten times a day.
You don't mind hearing us, do you?

10:32.340 --> 10:33.174
Of course not.

10:33.257 --> 10:34.925
He's far away right now, you see.

10:37.678 --> 10:40.097
-What is it?
-You look happy, that's all.

10:41.182 --> 10:42.850
Really? I do?

10:47.271 --> 10:49.523
Oh, right. I should wrap that up.

10:54.570 --> 10:58.157
We managed to sneak past his manager
out of the green room,

10:58.240 --> 10:59.992
but there were fans everywhere.

11:00.076 --> 11:02.411
I held my bias's hand and ran for it.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.706
We arrived at the parking lot,
but the fans were there too,

11:05.790 --> 11:09.877
so we ended up huddling down together
between the van and the wall.

11:09.960 --> 11:12.797
-I could hear his heart beating fast.
-Oh God.

11:13.297 --> 11:15.800
And with it, I could feel his warmth.

11:16.425 --> 11:17.426
And then…

11:18.052 --> 11:19.178
This is insane.

11:35.069 --> 11:36.445
Here?

11:38.531 --> 11:40.658
What? Is there a problem?

11:41.575 --> 11:43.327
No. There's no problem.

11:56.090 --> 11:58.551
Babe, wait.
What if my manager walks in on--

11:59.051 --> 11:59.885
Be quiet.

12:00.469 --> 12:01.929
Okay.

12:05.099 --> 12:06.434
Stay still.

12:25.077 --> 12:26.162
Stop.

12:26.245 --> 12:28.164
You… want to pick another one?

12:29.665 --> 12:30.875
Yes.

12:30.958 --> 12:32.710
Calm down a bit.

12:32.793 --> 12:37.381
Let's try just ten themes a week.

12:37.465 --> 12:39.467
How come? I have tons of free time.

12:41.218 --> 12:44.138
Well, at this rate,

12:44.638 --> 12:47.725
you'll have met all 900 of them
by next month.

12:47.808 --> 12:49.560
You know,

12:50.144 --> 12:51.979
I really like it here.

12:53.063 --> 12:54.064
I can see that.

12:54.148 --> 12:57.693
It's a massive dopamine boost.
My confidence is soaring.

12:58.360 --> 13:00.362
And no one here is calling me man-crazy,

13:00.446 --> 13:03.407
dissing me for not taking
my relationships seriously.

13:03.491 --> 13:05.242
I can just move on to the next guy.

13:06.702 --> 13:07.745
On top of all that,

13:07.828 --> 13:11.248
even when I try the themes
everyone else is having trouble with,

13:12.166 --> 13:14.585
I can clear them in one go.

13:15.252 --> 13:17.963
I really, really love that.

13:19.340 --> 13:21.342
Being overwhelmingly good at something.

13:21.926 --> 13:23.427
It's such a rush!

13:25.054 --> 13:27.306
Submit.

13:27.389 --> 13:28.432
THANK YOU

13:31.811 --> 13:35.272
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND 178TH THEME REVIEW
THE GUY NEXT DOOR

13:35.815 --> 13:37.983
592 LIKES, 930 COMMENTS

13:38.567 --> 13:41.320
What's this?
Why are there so many comments?

13:41.821 --> 13:43.823
YOUR POST JUST HIT 10,000 VIEWS!

13:47.785 --> 13:49.537
Your post just hit 10,000 views!

13:49.620 --> 13:52.456
Wait, what is happening right now?

13:57.294 --> 14:00.798
Who put up all these decorations,
and when?

14:01.841 --> 14:02.883
I wonder.

14:02.967 --> 14:04.593
What are you doing for Seollal?

14:05.886 --> 14:08.848
Me? I'm just going to eat tangerines
and read comic books.

14:09.807 --> 14:12.643
My mom told me not to come over
since she's going on a trip,

14:12.726 --> 14:16.230
so I'll be rotting away at home
for five days.

14:16.313 --> 14:18.816
Well, all the better.
Take the chance to rest.

14:23.696 --> 14:25.364
He offered to help us with this.

14:27.575 --> 14:31.328
I'll put the tree in the storeroom later.
Should I start with this one?

14:31.412 --> 14:32.246
Yes.

14:34.790 --> 14:36.542
Do you have plans for the holidays?

14:36.625 --> 14:38.919
I'm going to read comic books
and eat tangerines.

14:39.670 --> 14:41.046
What?

14:52.057 --> 14:53.309
You guys really…

14:57.688 --> 15:01.108
Whatever am I gonna do about you nerds?

15:01.817 --> 15:04.820
You're reading comic books
in the age of OTT platforms?

15:04.904 --> 15:08.324
Mr. Hwang keeps calling me uncultured,
and it's all because of you guys.

15:08.407 --> 15:11.118
Stop reading them now.
You guys have read enough.

15:12.161 --> 15:14.830
I'll go put these in the archives.

15:26.592 --> 15:28.469
It's dangerous out there.

15:32.556 --> 15:34.725
What are you doing?
You can't follow me in here.

15:34.808 --> 15:37.144
What's wrong?
I'm only here to put this away.

15:37.227 --> 15:39.396
Hey! Then I'll go out first.

15:51.951 --> 15:52.952
Wait a second.

16:06.090 --> 16:08.634
-What if someone sees us?
-Just act natural.

16:08.717 --> 16:10.219
That's easier said than done.

16:11.303 --> 16:13.639
Man, I'm a terrible liar.

16:14.139 --> 16:15.975
The office life will be the death of me.

16:19.603 --> 16:20.938
Should we just get caught?

16:22.398 --> 16:23.482
You are insane.

16:45.838 --> 16:46.922
Sweetie.

16:50.801 --> 16:52.720
-Are you okay?
-Huh?

16:55.889 --> 16:56.724
I am okay.

17:05.774 --> 17:07.443
Having fun teasing me?

17:08.068 --> 17:09.194
What about dinner?

17:10.279 --> 17:13.282
I have a meeting with Ms. Yun.
Eat without me.

17:14.658 --> 17:16.243
I'll pick you up later.

17:26.420 --> 17:27.921
Order some food for me.

17:28.005 --> 17:30.466
My wrist is killing me!

17:30.966 --> 17:33.886
This industry overworks its authors
way too much.

17:33.969 --> 17:36.638
I'll reduce the number of panels
in my next contract.

17:37.139 --> 17:39.516
Soon, I won't even be able to
hold up a spoon.

17:39.600 --> 17:41.769
Yun Song's contract is almost up.

17:41.852 --> 17:44.813
At this rate, we'll never renew
the contract on good terms.

17:46.774 --> 17:50.611
Have you talked to Director Hwang
about your next contract yet?

17:51.320 --> 17:54.490
No. Come to think of it,
he hasn't mentioned it yet.

17:55.282 --> 17:56.283
I'm sure he will soon.

18:07.252 --> 18:10.506
Ms. Yun, if we wait until the next season,
it will be too late.

18:11.340 --> 18:12.758
Do you have a solution?

18:14.468 --> 18:17.721
Do you remember
when PlanC first joined us on Fridays?

18:18.305 --> 18:22.559
It's time for us to find out what's wrong
and make changes like we did then.

18:23.227 --> 18:25.813
This is something you need to do.

18:25.896 --> 18:28.649
There has to be something only you can do.

18:28.732 --> 18:29.566
Seo.

18:30.442 --> 18:31.985
Are you trying to dump it on me?

18:33.070 --> 18:36.240
It's not like that.
I'm also going to give it my all.

18:36.740 --> 18:41.411
But still, please don't forget
that this is your work.

18:51.505 --> 18:54.466
I just don't know anymore.
This is too difficult.

18:56.885 --> 18:58.303
Can I take a look?

18:59.388 --> 19:00.222
Sure.

19:04.476 --> 19:06.228
THE MAN TO KNOW
STORY DEVELOPMENT OUTLINE

19:07.396 --> 19:08.397
What do you think?

19:09.231 --> 19:11.733
It might catch attention
for a little while, but…

19:12.651 --> 19:13.652
But that's it, huh?

19:15.279 --> 19:16.280
Yes.

19:18.407 --> 19:20.075
This won't do at all.

19:21.702 --> 19:24.329
We need to get through this
if we want to beat PlanC.

19:25.622 --> 19:28.458
Stop looking. I've already shown
too much to my competition.

19:32.296 --> 19:33.130
Adorable.

19:34.590 --> 19:35.424
What?

19:36.341 --> 19:37.176
I mean,

19:38.177 --> 19:39.428
why are you so adorable?

19:42.055 --> 19:45.475
Hey now, that's no way to talk about
someone who's working hard.

19:45.559 --> 19:47.060
-Hmph.
-"Hey now"?

19:57.571 --> 20:01.158
Could you draw a picture for me too?
Like the one you gave to Hwany.

20:01.241 --> 20:02.075
Sure.

20:02.159 --> 20:04.161
Really? You mean it?

20:04.244 --> 20:05.078
Yes.

20:06.747 --> 20:08.749
Would you like me to draw you?

20:10.250 --> 20:11.084
What?

20:13.503 --> 20:14.755
Want me to draw you?

20:20.010 --> 20:21.094
You don't like that?

20:23.555 --> 20:24.973
No, I love it.

20:36.568 --> 20:38.904
This is something you need to do.

20:38.987 --> 20:40.906
There has to be something only you can do.

20:47.871 --> 20:49.122
Oh God, seriously.

20:49.665 --> 20:54.086
Why does everyone keep bitching at me?
For goodness' sake.

21:03.345 --> 21:06.431
Why does everyone keep bitching at me?

21:07.266 --> 21:10.852
I mean, everyone with a mouth
keeps spouting off at the author!

21:10.936 --> 21:12.271
Easy for them to say.

21:12.354 --> 21:15.065
I'd like to see them try.
They'd manage, what, three panels?

21:15.148 --> 21:18.151
No, not even a single panel,
and they keep giving me orders.

21:18.235 --> 21:22.531
I work hard, they say, "Make it fun."
I make it fun, they say, "Work faster."

21:22.614 --> 21:25.701
Damn it! It's so annoying, seriously!

21:37.546 --> 21:38.964
Going on another hiatus, then?

21:39.881 --> 21:42.801
No. I mean, I have to push through.

21:44.219 --> 21:46.471
So you don't put that producer
in a hard spot?

21:47.306 --> 21:48.390
It's not that, but…

21:49.725 --> 21:52.853
You know,
I just don't want to let her down.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.481
Why's that? Because she's your friend?

21:59.359 --> 22:02.654
You've got such a kind heart, Song.

22:03.363 --> 22:07.117
You're the only person who says I'm kind.

22:07.200 --> 22:09.411
People don't know
what they're talking about.

22:10.787 --> 22:11.705
I should get going.

22:12.289 --> 22:13.749
Huh? Where to?

22:13.832 --> 22:16.335
You should work hard
to not let your friend down,

22:16.418 --> 22:18.670
and I should help you get motivated.

22:19.588 --> 22:21.465
Come see me at my workplace in a bit.

22:30.140 --> 22:32.517
What's this? He told me to come here.

23:19.940 --> 23:21.316
Oh my!

23:23.819 --> 23:24.694
You're here.

23:26.238 --> 23:28.949
What's this? Hansel and Gretel?

23:31.076 --> 23:34.287
Nothing beats sweet treats
when you're feeling down.

23:35.414 --> 23:36.832
It seems to be working.

24:02.274 --> 24:04.276
HANDMADE TOFU RESTAURANT

24:07.070 --> 24:10.574
Why does this guy always tag along
when our team comes out to eat?

24:14.119 --> 24:17.247
Come on, Naemo's a small company.
We're all on the same team.

24:17.330 --> 24:19.416
Oh, right you are.

24:22.210 --> 24:23.795
This is a place where any romance…

24:23.879 --> 24:25.380
That ad is everywhere these days.

24:25.964 --> 24:27.799
There are 900 themes just for you.

24:27.883 --> 24:31.928
It's getting a ton of buzz right now,
so they are striking while the iron's hot.

24:32.804 --> 24:35.932
I think that's our real competition,
not the other webtoon platforms.

24:37.309 --> 24:39.102
Why would anyone use that anyway?

24:40.645 --> 24:41.938
What do you mean, why?

24:42.522 --> 24:45.734
What girl wouldn't want to date
an attractive guy?

24:46.234 --> 24:47.819
Are you a subscriber?

24:47.903 --> 24:50.030
-Just eat your food.
-Okay.

24:52.699 --> 24:55.785
So, who will you be dating today?

24:56.620 --> 24:58.830
It's been a while. Go for drinks?

24:58.914 --> 25:00.081
Seriously?

25:00.165 --> 25:02.501
Why even ask? We definitely should!

25:04.211 --> 25:07.631
What time do you finish work today?
Join us as soon as you can.

25:07.714 --> 25:10.300
I can't promise anything.
Ms. Yun is so unpredictable.

25:10.383 --> 25:12.177
Goodness, you poor thing.

25:12.677 --> 25:15.096
Kyeong-nam, you should come with us.

25:15.180 --> 25:18.183
I also have a deadline.
I should head back with her.

25:18.266 --> 25:20.602
How come?
Hwany's already submitted his work.

25:21.311 --> 25:23.396
-What?
-Look.

25:23.480 --> 25:26.483
Going home now! Enjoy today's episode!

25:30.028 --> 25:32.030
Since when did he post that kind of stuff?

25:35.116 --> 25:37.869
I guess that means
you can come with us, right?

25:37.953 --> 25:39.079
Call me when you finish.

25:39.162 --> 25:40.247
-Let's go!
-Let's go.

25:40.330 --> 25:41.248
Wait, I…

25:42.958 --> 25:43.792
I…

25:44.751 --> 25:46.545
To that place we went to last time.

25:46.628 --> 25:47.462
Okay!

25:55.512 --> 25:57.639
DON'T BE TOO LATE, BUT TAKE YOUR TIME!

25:59.307 --> 26:00.892
Maybe I pushed her too much.

26:09.401 --> 26:11.069
Seo Mi-rae!

26:18.451 --> 26:20.036
Seo Mi-rae!

26:21.037 --> 26:23.290
Did you hear something just now?

26:25.166 --> 26:26.293
Sorry?

26:26.835 --> 26:27.794
I didn't hear

26:28.837 --> 26:29.921
a thing.

26:30.005 --> 26:31.381
I see.

26:31.464 --> 26:32.799
Am I hearing things?

26:42.976 --> 26:44.477
Why did you come here?

26:44.561 --> 26:45.979
Wow, it's Seo Mi-rae.

26:46.062 --> 26:49.566
I put my finger on this thingy,
but it wouldn't open.

26:50.066 --> 26:52.485
-Thank God.
-It's supposed to open, right?

26:53.028 --> 26:55.697
How much did you drink?
Why are you so drunk?

27:01.703 --> 27:03.371
Enjoy.

27:06.124 --> 27:09.336
I've never seen anyone get drunk
and go home before the food is served.

27:09.419 --> 27:10.670
I know, right?

27:10.754 --> 27:13.340
Why did you offer him a drink
as soon as we got here?

27:13.423 --> 27:15.342
Who knew one glass would knock him out?

27:18.845 --> 27:21.097
I wonder if he got home safe.

27:38.990 --> 27:39.991
Oh God!

27:48.083 --> 27:49.042
I'm fine though.

27:49.125 --> 27:51.795
No. The fact that you came here
means you're not fine.

27:52.504 --> 27:54.964
What did you even tell the others
before you left?

27:56.132 --> 27:57.884
I told them I was heading home.

27:58.760 --> 27:59.761
You did well.

28:00.512 --> 28:03.098
Stay here until I finish my work, okay?

28:03.181 --> 28:04.516
So I did well?

28:05.183 --> 28:07.102
-Stay.
-Stay.

28:07.185 --> 28:09.354
-Stay.
-Stay.

28:16.069 --> 28:17.904
Hey. I'll be going home now.

28:17.987 --> 28:19.739
Sure. Good night.

28:23.702 --> 28:26.371
-Get home safe. See you tomorrow.
-Sure.

28:26.955 --> 28:29.040
-Good work today.
-Goodbye, then.

28:51.312 --> 28:53.898
Really? It's only ten o'clock.

29:18.256 --> 29:19.674
Have you sobered up a bit?

29:20.175 --> 29:22.886
You really shouldn't have come here.
That was so close.

29:23.553 --> 29:27.140
I'm sorry. I just missed you so much.

29:29.017 --> 29:31.728
Oh, you. You did well.

29:32.228 --> 29:33.563
Let's go now.

29:33.646 --> 29:36.649
Ms. Yun submitted her work early,
so I'm heading out.

29:46.367 --> 29:48.203
Did you match them up again?

29:48.286 --> 29:49.537
I think I might have.

29:49.621 --> 29:51.873
So how many did you match up today?

29:58.463 --> 30:00.799
I can go by myself.

30:00.882 --> 30:02.550
I should still walk you all the way.

30:03.051 --> 30:04.135
Okay, then.

30:08.515 --> 30:11.017
-Haven't you forgotten something?
-What do you mean?

30:13.353 --> 30:14.354
Just go already.

30:20.318 --> 30:21.152
Anything else?

30:22.529 --> 30:24.280
Keep that up, and I won't let you go.

30:37.460 --> 30:38.795
I'm home.

30:38.878 --> 30:41.923
I hereby forbid you from drinking
without me. See you tomorrow.

30:46.427 --> 30:47.262
See you tomorrow.

30:49.889 --> 30:53.518
Sheesh, he never sends me
so much as a heart.

30:59.148 --> 31:02.485
1: THE MAN TO KNOW
2: PLANC

31:06.906 --> 31:07.740
Hey.

31:08.283 --> 31:10.159
Ms. Yun, have you seen the rankings?

31:10.910 --> 31:12.829
Yes, I just saw.

31:12.912 --> 31:15.164
I'm exhausted after working all night.

31:15.248 --> 31:17.166
Our readers are loving it right now.

31:17.250 --> 31:19.085
I knew you could do it.

31:19.586 --> 31:23.256
But how did you even come up with
something like that at the perfect moment?

31:23.339 --> 31:26.301
A chef with a big heart
who's the polar opposite of Choi Si-woo

31:26.384 --> 31:27.802
as the second male lead.

31:27.886 --> 31:30.555
The hotel will make a great setup
for a love triangle.

31:30.638 --> 31:31.639
It just…

31:34.058 --> 31:35.476
came to me out of the blue.

31:35.977 --> 31:38.187
We all have those days to be grateful for.

31:38.938 --> 31:41.107
Well, I'm loving it.

31:41.608 --> 31:42.525
Glad to hear that.

31:42.609 --> 31:45.278
Enjoy the holidays.
Let's keep at it when we get back.

31:46.571 --> 31:47.405
Ms. Yun.

31:47.989 --> 31:50.909
I'm so glad to be working with you.

31:51.993 --> 31:53.411
Didn't expect that.

31:54.162 --> 31:55.955
Go to bed. I'm hanging up now.

31:56.039 --> 31:56.998
Okay. Good night.

32:02.795 --> 32:04.005
Awesome!

32:13.765 --> 32:14.766
Congratulations.

32:17.936 --> 32:19.187
Thank you.

32:21.940 --> 32:23.149
You've done well.

32:24.651 --> 32:25.652
What?

32:29.405 --> 32:32.075
What's up with him?
That heart emoji came out of nowhere.

32:36.704 --> 32:39.457
Everything is just perfect.

32:47.048 --> 32:49.217
Is it okay for me to be this happy?

33:07.235 --> 33:09.195
-Hey, so--
-What am I going to do?

33:09.779 --> 33:11.656
-Huh?
-What am I supposed to do?

33:14.909 --> 33:17.578
What do you mean? Just work hard.

33:18.371 --> 33:21.708
Damn it. You never have a game plan
for anything, ever.

33:21.791 --> 33:23.459
No author needs to have a game plan.

33:23.543 --> 33:27.213
Just have fun, work hard, and draw well.

33:27.296 --> 33:29.716
God, just forget I said anything.

33:34.095 --> 33:35.930
Why are you putting your coat on?

33:36.556 --> 33:37.390
Huh?

33:43.980 --> 33:46.399
Isn't it a bit chilly in here?

33:46.482 --> 33:48.109
Why are you being so weird?

33:49.277 --> 33:50.945
What do you mean?

33:51.029 --> 33:53.489
You've been fidgeting
like you need a bathroom break.

33:53.573 --> 33:54.866
Do you have somewhere to be?

33:55.783 --> 33:56.617
Huh?

34:01.789 --> 34:03.374
I have to leave before dinner.

34:03.458 --> 34:07.045
Come on! Such a buzzkill.
We finally found the time to hang out.

34:08.254 --> 34:11.758
I can't believe you used to go on
about him being a jerk.

34:11.841 --> 34:13.551
This is why I never believe you.

34:13.634 --> 34:16.220
Hey, that was, like, ages ago.

34:16.304 --> 34:18.431
It wasn't even that long ago.

34:22.185 --> 34:23.019
Hey, but really--

34:23.102 --> 34:24.187
You have to go soon?

34:24.896 --> 34:29.233
Don't worry. I'll let you off soon.
I'm busy too, you know.

34:30.234 --> 34:31.069
Why are you busy?

34:32.653 --> 34:35.323
-I also have a date.
-You said you were going home.

34:35.406 --> 34:37.325
That's right. An at-home date.

34:37.408 --> 34:40.495
You said you weren't dating,
and you're already having a guy over?

34:41.496 --> 34:42.747
I guess I am.

34:53.466 --> 34:55.885
Yeah, I think you should get a set today.

34:56.385 --> 34:57.220
What?

34:58.262 --> 35:00.264
Hey! I was just looking.

35:00.348 --> 35:02.517
The red one?
What do you think of that one?

35:04.102 --> 35:05.353
I'm good. Just hurry up.

35:05.436 --> 35:07.688
-I think it'll look good on you!
-Hurry up.

35:20.576 --> 35:21.911
A little late, huh? Sorry.

35:21.994 --> 35:23.037
Come on in.

35:26.415 --> 35:28.084
-You must be cold.
-First, a gift.

35:46.102 --> 35:46.936
Are you hungry?

35:48.521 --> 35:49.814
I'm good for now.

35:50.773 --> 35:52.775
Tell me if you get hungry.
I'll cook for you.

35:55.403 --> 35:58.072
No, you're the guest.
I should be the one to cook.

35:59.198 --> 36:01.951
I'll make you tteokguk.
I bought the ingredients.

36:03.202 --> 36:05.121
What? You know how to do that too?

36:07.582 --> 36:09.167
Man, I'm hungry.

36:16.841 --> 36:18.593
I don't want to age another year.

36:19.427 --> 36:21.179
Careful, I'm holding a knife.

36:22.597 --> 36:23.764
Fine.

36:34.817 --> 36:36.235
Then shall we eat later?

36:38.279 --> 36:39.280
Shall we?

38:37.481 --> 38:39.567
Sir, I think you should
take a look at this.

38:41.569 --> 38:43.279
CONQUERING BOD BY BOYFRIENDKILLER

38:43.362 --> 38:44.864
What am I looking at?

38:45.364 --> 38:48.034
Apparently, it's all the rage
among our subscribers.

38:48.117 --> 38:48.951
What is it?

38:49.035 --> 38:51.120
Basically, it's like a walkthrough.

38:51.203 --> 38:55.124
It seems the subscribers who had trouble
with their dates are really into it.

38:55.207 --> 38:57.543
But it's not a game.
Who needs a walkthrough?

38:58.044 --> 39:00.755
This user must be treating it like a game.

39:05.343 --> 39:06.427
Eun-ho.

39:07.845 --> 39:09.472
Do you have someone you like?

39:19.732 --> 39:24.070
There's only one thing we need to
keep in mind in Boyfriend on Demand.

39:24.153 --> 39:25.905
Want to try liking me?

39:30.993 --> 39:31.994
Sure.

39:32.078 --> 39:36.332
No matter how desirable a guy may be,
you are the star of the show.

39:44.632 --> 39:47.385
What do you think? Do you like it?

39:48.427 --> 39:49.595
Yes.

39:49.678 --> 39:52.014
I'll take the necklace,

39:52.098 --> 39:54.683
but can you throw in this hotel too?

39:55.726 --> 39:59.647
So you don't need to feel intimidated
just because he is a chaebol…

40:21.669 --> 40:22.670
Bang!

40:27.133 --> 40:29.969
…or nervous about him being an NIS agent.

40:30.052 --> 40:31.637
Are you okay?

40:50.614 --> 40:53.951
Ms. Lee Ji-yeon,
you have obtained a love triangle item.

40:54.034 --> 40:54.910
Oh my.

41:05.463 --> 41:07.882
Are you worried about two-timing?

41:08.924 --> 41:09.758
Well, don't be.

41:10.342 --> 41:13.554
Dating two men isn't that bad.
I've done a lot worse.

41:19.727 --> 41:22.396
So here's my recommendation.

41:22.480 --> 41:27.151
"At night, play the love triangle theme
and pop two items to end up with four…"

41:27.234 --> 41:28.861
Four? Four men?

41:28.944 --> 41:30.863
Who… Who is this person?

41:30.946 --> 41:31.989
We're investigating.

41:32.072 --> 41:33.908
This must be all she ever thinks about.

41:33.991 --> 41:35.910
A dating sim writer? Or a web novelist?

41:35.993 --> 41:39.330
If this kind of fast-paced dating
becomes a trend,

41:39.413 --> 41:41.665
the long-term subscription
will inevitably drop.

41:41.749 --> 41:44.293
She dated 220 men in two months?

41:45.294 --> 41:46.545
Is she out of her mind?

41:59.266 --> 42:00.100
What's this?

42:00.184 --> 42:02.645
Turns out I left one out
when I gave you those books.

42:02.728 --> 42:04.980
I'd been wondering about that. Thanks.

42:05.898 --> 42:08.192
I'll see you tonight.
I have a meeting to attend.

42:08.275 --> 42:09.109
Okay.

42:34.468 --> 42:35.886
-Ms. Seo.
-Huh?

42:35.970 --> 42:38.180
Yes. What is it?

42:38.264 --> 42:40.599
An article just came out.

42:40.683 --> 42:42.560
An article? What article?

42:42.643 --> 42:44.812
I think you need to see this right away.

42:50.818 --> 42:53.112
TMTK ACCUSED OF PLAGIARIZING
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND

42:53.195 --> 42:55.948
Famous author Yun Song
has been caught up in another scandal.

42:56.031 --> 42:57.992
Several posts pointed out the similarities

42:58.075 --> 43:01.495
between a new male character
in her hit webtoon, The Man to Know,

43:01.579 --> 43:06.208
and a character from Boyfriend on Demand,
the dating subscription service.

43:06.292 --> 43:10.379
The allegations claim that
the character's stature, thick eyebrows,

43:10.462 --> 43:14.508
and occupation as a five-star hotel chef
all come together to make him

43:14.592 --> 43:17.511
a carbon copy of a character
from Boyfriend on Demand.

43:18.304 --> 43:19.847
This device is switched off.

43:20.639 --> 43:22.725
Is Ms. Yun not picking up?

43:22.808 --> 43:24.101
What are we going to do?

43:24.977 --> 43:25.978
-What's going on?
-Sir.

43:26.061 --> 43:28.480
-Hello?
-Hey, is what they're saying true?

43:28.564 --> 43:30.482
-I'll call them right now.
-Do it now!

43:30.566 --> 43:33.986
Call the reporters right now
and find out what happened.

43:34.069 --> 43:37.072
Hold on. Can anyone reach Yun Song?

43:37.156 --> 43:40.576
Has she really been on
this Boyfriend on Demand thing?

43:47.333 --> 43:48.709
FEELINGS ARE NOW A PRODUCT

43:48.792 --> 43:50.836
POPULAR WEBTOON AUTHOR YUN SONG UNDER FIRE

43:51.795 --> 43:54.381
Our birth rates are low as it is.
This is unacceptable.

43:54.465 --> 43:56.383
What's this got to do
with low birth rates?

43:56.467 --> 44:00.429
It's giving people such high standards
that they don't even want to date anymore.

44:00.512 --> 44:04.808
The subscription fee is so high.
It's left countless young people in debt.

44:04.892 --> 44:08.103
How do you afford the subscription?
Are your parents paying for you?

44:08.187 --> 44:10.105
-You're so pathetic.
-Pathetic?

44:10.189 --> 44:13.150
Goofing around in the virtual world.
I bet she's a total loser.

44:13.233 --> 44:14.318
Loser?

44:16.779 --> 44:18.614
You lousy little shits!

44:20.449 --> 44:21.283
Where is she?

44:22.743 --> 44:23.577
I don't know.

44:24.244 --> 44:27.498
I waited, thinking she might show up,
but she didn't.

44:28.666 --> 44:30.417
What are we going to do?

44:31.251 --> 44:33.712
It's going to be okay. Let me come inside.

44:59.780 --> 45:03.742
Are you kidding? So this was the boyfriend
she bragged about back then.

45:03.826 --> 45:05.160
I can't even…

45:05.828 --> 45:09.498
Didn't she get all preachy on us, saying
that our lives are duller than hers?

45:10.374 --> 45:13.335
Man, she turned out to be
one hell of a woman.

45:13.419 --> 45:15.379
That's what I call a poker face.

45:15.462 --> 45:17.798
-Did you even prepare for this meeting?
-Hey.

45:18.298 --> 45:20.551
Isn't this going to hurt So-yeong as well?

45:21.218 --> 45:23.303
I mean, think about it.

45:23.387 --> 45:27.391
If TMTK were to get cancelled,
So-yeong would end up jobless, right?

45:27.474 --> 45:29.435
Well, I guess that could happen.

45:30.644 --> 45:32.896
No, we can't let that happen. No way.

45:34.273 --> 45:35.149
Hey, don't do it.

45:35.232 --> 45:37.109
So-yeong, are you doing okay?

45:37.192 --> 45:41.196
If you find yourself in need of a new job,
I'll set you up with a good one.

45:41.280 --> 45:42.114
Don't send that.

45:42.197 --> 45:45.409
What on earth was she thinking?
How could she screw you over like this?

45:45.492 --> 45:47.745
Please get back to me.
I'm worried about you.

45:53.000 --> 45:55.252
She didn't screw me over. Got it?

45:55.335 --> 45:58.422
Besides, I'm also on Boyfriend on Demand,
so mind your own business!

45:58.505 --> 45:59.339
Huh?

46:00.090 --> 46:00.924
Kyeong-nam.

46:03.927 --> 46:06.013
God, I told you not to send it.

46:18.108 --> 46:18.942
Hello.

46:19.610 --> 46:20.736
Have you eaten?

46:22.696 --> 46:23.530
No.

46:25.407 --> 46:26.533
Where are you?

46:26.617 --> 46:28.285
At Ms. Yun's studio.

46:28.786 --> 46:32.623
So-yeong just left,
but I think I'll wait a little longer.

46:34.208 --> 46:36.460
She might show up late, after all.

46:39.505 --> 46:43.592
If you just got off work,
can you do me a favor?

46:43.675 --> 46:45.511
Of course. What is it?

46:46.011 --> 46:49.181
The thumb drive with our meeting notes
is at my place,

46:49.264 --> 46:51.266
and I want to check them right now.

46:51.350 --> 46:54.061
But I'm worried Ms. Yun might come here
while I'm away.

46:54.144 --> 46:59.107
I'm sorry, but could you go to my place
and send them to me?

46:59.900 --> 47:01.735
I'll head over right now.

47:01.819 --> 47:02.653
Thank you.

47:04.238 --> 47:06.406
I think I'll be home really late.

47:06.907 --> 47:09.076
But can you still wait for me?

47:10.327 --> 47:12.412
Sure. I'll see you later.

47:12.496 --> 47:13.413
See you.

47:40.065 --> 47:41.775
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND

48:01.962 --> 48:03.422
Why would anyone use that anyway?

48:04.840 --> 48:06.091
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND REVIEW

48:06.174 --> 48:08.677
TRIAL TIME: 50 HOURS
USER SATISFACTION SURVEY

48:13.932 --> 48:14.766
Damn it.

48:32.993 --> 48:34.161
Damn it. Come on!

48:44.087 --> 48:45.589
Why isn't he picking up?

48:51.595 --> 48:52.888
SEO MI-RAE

49:07.653 --> 49:09.112
Taxi!

49:12.282 --> 49:13.533
Yongsan, please.

49:16.161 --> 49:17.412
Pick up!

49:21.208 --> 49:22.626
8. REVIEW

49:40.227 --> 49:41.061
Damn it.

49:48.568 --> 49:49.403
Mi-rae.

49:52.364 --> 49:53.198
Why are you here?

49:53.865 --> 49:57.285
Well, your phone…
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

49:58.662 --> 49:59.997
I was busy cleaning.

50:11.216 --> 50:12.050
Are you all right?

50:15.345 --> 50:16.471
Thank you.

50:21.685 --> 50:22.602
Is something wrong?

50:24.438 --> 50:25.856
Is it because of Ms. Yun?

50:26.898 --> 50:27.899
No.

50:27.983 --> 50:29.693
Or did the director say something?

50:36.450 --> 50:38.535
Why did you race home? I'm worried.

50:43.290 --> 50:44.166
It's just that

50:45.834 --> 50:47.085
I was scared.

50:48.837 --> 50:49.921
Of what?

50:53.467 --> 50:54.342
Just

50:55.635 --> 50:57.220
scared of everything.

51:07.314 --> 51:09.149
I'm sure Ms. Yun will be okay.

51:11.818 --> 51:15.405
I can't tell him what I'm scared of.

51:16.364 --> 51:19.201
I just can't bring myself to tell him.

52:38.155 --> 52:39.322
When was this taken?

52:41.074 --> 52:42.325
She looks good in it.

52:47.539 --> 52:51.543
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I LIKE YOU

52:59.426 --> 53:00.927
I was a little mad at you.

53:01.595 --> 53:04.598
For not even answering me
when I asked you to come with me.

53:05.891 --> 53:08.643
So I was just going to get over you, but

53:09.895 --> 53:11.229
it's harder than I thought.

53:12.480 --> 53:13.565
I miss you.

54:14.918 --> 54:15.919
Seo Mi-rae.

54:36.606 --> 54:37.732
What took you so long?

54:39.067 --> 54:39.901
What?

54:43.613 --> 54:44.531
How is this…

58:01.561 --> 58:06.566
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon
